******
[1] New Zealand apples banned while committee investigates fireblight
Date: Wed 20 Jun 2007
Source: Australian Broadcasting Corporation News [edited]
<http://abc.net.au/news/stories/2007/06/20/1957209.htm?section=justin>

A Senate Committee has sided with fruit growers in Victoria's Goulburn
Valley who are concerned about the spread of disease if New Zealand apples
are allowed into Australia.
The Rural Affairs Committee has tabled its report into the decision by the
Australian Quarantine Inspection Service (AQIS) to lift the import ban. In
the report, the committee says it was not convinced by AQIS's argument that
diseases like fireblight would come into Australia but not spread.
The committee also states concerns that AQIS ignored scientific evidence
during an appeal against the decision by the fruit industry.
The committee has asked that no New Zealand apple imports go ahead until it
makes a final determination.
--
